Package provided.jxMaps.utils

Interface IMapNavigator

  • public interface IMapNavigator
    An encapsulation of the movement and event-based actions of an associated map. DO NOT INSTANTIATE OR IMPLEMENT THIS FACTORY YOURSELF! This factory MUST be created by a IJxMapsComponentFactory to properly tie to and manage the associated Map object.

      • addMapEvent

        com.teamdev.jxmaps.MapEvent addMapEvent​(java.lang.String eventID,
                                        IAction<com.teamdev.jxmaps.Map> handlerFn)
        Add a map event to the map
        Parameters:
        eventID - The desired event type, selected from the constants in IJxMaps_Defs.IEvent. DO NOT USE "MAGIC" values!
        handlerFn - The action to perform when the event is invoked. The map is given to this function upon invocation.
        Returns:
        A new MapEvent instance that encapsulates the event ID and handlerFn. This MapEvent can be used to remove the installed event.

      • removeMapEvent

        void removeMapEvent​(com.teamdev.jxmaps.MapEvent mapEvt)
        Remove a map event from the map
        Parameters:
        mapEvt - The MapEvent to remove. This should be the MapEvent returned by addMapEvent().

      • addMapMouseEvent

        com.teamdev.jxmaps.MapMouseEvent addMapMouseEvent​(java.lang.String eventID,
                                                  IAction<com.teamdev.jxmaps.MouseEvent> handlerFn)
        Add a map mouse event to the map
        Parameters:
        eventID - The desired event type, selected from the constants in IJxMaps_Defs.IEvent. DO NOT USE "MAGIC" values!
        handlerFn - The action to perform when the event is invoked. The MouseEvent is given to this function upon invocation. Note that the map is available via MouseEvent.getMap().
        Returns:
        A new MapMouseEvent instance that encapsulates the event ID and handlerFn. This MapMouseEvent can be used to remove the installed event.

      • removeMapMouseEvent

        void removeMapMouseEvent​(com.teamdev.jxmaps.MapMouseEvent mapMouseEvt)
        Remove a map mouse event from the map
        Parameters:
        mapMouseEvt - The MapEvent to remove. This should be the MapMouseEvent returned by addMapMouseEvent().

      • serviceGeoCoderRequest

        void serviceGeoCoderRequest​(com.teamdev.jxmaps.GeocoderRequest request,
                            java.util.function.BiConsumer<com.teamdev.jxmaps.GeocoderResult[],​com.teamdev.jxmaps.GeocoderStatus> onCompleteHandler)
        Perform the Geocoding service request as defined by the given GeocodeRequest object. The geocoder results are processed by the onCompleteHandler when the request is complete.
        Parameters:
        request - The GeocodeRequest object that one wished to be serviced.
        onCompleteHandler - A BiConsumer<GeocoderResult[], GeocoderStatus> that takes the results of the geocoder request servicing and processes them.

      • servicePlacesSearch

        void servicePlacesSearch​(com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlaceSearchRequest request,
                         java.util.function.BiConsumer<com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlaceResult[],​com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlacesServiceStatus> onCompleteHandler)
        Perform an asynchronous search of nearby places using the given request object. The results are processed by the given onCompleteHandler. When invoked, the onCompleteHandler's parameters are an array of result objects and a status object.
        NOTE: JxMaps does not currently support pagination of results, so only the first page of results is ever returned. DO NOT ATTEMPT SEARCHES WHERE MORE THAN ABOUT A DOZEN RESULTS ARE EXPECTED!
        Parameters:
        request - The desired search request
        onCompleteHandler - A handler function to process any returned results.

      • servicePlacesSearch

        Perform an asynchronous search of nearby places using the given request object. The results are processed by the given onCompleteHandler. When invoked, the onCompleteHandler's parameters are an array of result objects and a status object.
        NOTE: JxMaps does not currently support pagination of results, so only the first page of results is ever returned. DO NOT ATTEMPT SEARCHES WHERE MORE THAN ABOUT A DOZEN RESULTS ARE EXPECTED!
        Parameters:
        request - The desired search request
        onCompleteHandler - A handler function to process any returned results.

      • servicePlacesSearch

        void servicePlacesSearch​(com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlaceDetailsRequest request,
                         java.util.function.BiConsumer<com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlaceResult[],​com.teamdev.jxmaps.PlacesServiceStatus> onCompleteHandler)
        Perform an asynchronous search for the details of a given place using the given request object. The results are processed by the given onCompleteHandler. When invoked, the onCompleteHandler's parameters are an array of result objects and a status object.
        NOTE: Since only one place is being searched, the results array will have at most one element.
        Parameters:
        request - The desired search request
        onCompleteHandler - A handler function to process any returned results.
